articles.title: This is how much I'm a Celebrity paid to use Gwrych Castle - and what the ITV fee will be used for - North Wales Live
articles.description: Dr Mark Baker, chairman of the Gwrych Castle Preservation Trust, hopes to put the fee towards renovation work
articles.content:
Gwrych Castle has been paid £300,000 by ITV as part of its I'm a Celebrity contract this year.
The estate in Abergele is the location for the upcoming series of the show, which will start on Sunday.… [+2691 chars]
